'''ᱨᱚᱢᱭᱟ ᱠᱨᱤᱥᱱᱚᱱ''' (ᱡᱟᱱᱟᱢ ᱑᱕ ᱥᱮᱯᱴᱮᱢᱵᱚᱨ ᱑᱙᱗᱐),<!--DO NOT change this without providing a source--><ref name="bdt" /> ᱫᱚ ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛᱤᱭᱟ. ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱬ ᱟᱠᱴᱨᱮᱥ ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱱᱩᱭ ᱫᱚ [[ᱛᱮᱞᱩᱜᱩ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱛᱮᱞᱩᱜᱩ]], [[ᱛᱟᱢᱤᱞ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱛᱟᱢᱤᱞ]], [[ᱠᱟᱱᱱᱟᱰᱟ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱠᱟᱱᱱᱟᱰᱟ]], [[ᱢᱟᱞᱟᱭᱚᱞᱚᱢ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱢᱟᱞᱟᱭᱚᱞᱚᱢ]] ᱟᱨ [[ᱦᱤᱱᱫᱤ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ|ᱦᱤᱱᱫᱤ]] ᱮᱢᱟᱱ ᱢᱚᱬᱮ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ ᱯᱟ.ᱨᱥᱤ ᱛᱮ ᱒᱖᱐ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ ᱠᱷᱟᱱ ᱵᱤᱥᱛᱤ ᱜᱮ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱟ ᱾<!--Please do not change the languages order without discussing at the talk page--> ᱨᱚᱢᱭᱟ ᱫᱚ ᱯᱩᱱᱭᱟ. [[ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱯᱷᱮᱭᱟᱨ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ ᱥᱟᱣᱩᱛᱷ|ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱯᱷᱮᱭᱟᱨ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ]], ᱯᱮᱭᱟ [[ᱱᱚᱱᱫᱤ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ]] ᱟᱨ ᱢᱤᱫ [[ᱛᱟᱢᱤᱞ ᱱᱟᱰᱩ ᱯᱚᱱᱚᱛ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ]] ᱧᱟᱢ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱟ ᱾  ᱱᱩᱭ ᱫᱚ ᱛᱮᱞᱩᱜᱩ ᱟᱨ ᱛᱟᱢᱤᱞᱤ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱤᱱᱰᱚᱥᱴᱨᱤ ᱨᱮ '''ᱨᱚᱢᱭᱟ ᱠᱨᱤᱥᱱᱚᱱ''' ᱢᱮᱱᱛᱮ ᱧᱩᱭᱩᱢ ᱪᱟᱢᱯᱷᱮᱞ ᱠᱟᱱ ᱛᱟᱭᱟ ᱾<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://telanganatoday.com/ramya-krishna-joins-romantic-for-shoot-in-goa | title=Ramya Krishna joins Romantic for shoot in Goa |date=11 November 2019 |accessdate=28 November 2019}}</ref>

''[[ᱯᱚᱫᱚᱭᱟᱯᱯᱟ]]'' ᱨᱮ ᱱᱤᱲᱟᱢᱵᱚᱨᱤ ᱠᱮᱨᱮᱠᱴᱚᱨ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱠᱷᱟ.ᱛᱤᱨ ᱟ.ᱰᱤ ᱱᱟᱯᱟᱭ ᱧᱩᱛᱩᱢ ᱟᱱ ᱛᱟᱦᱮᱸᱫ ᱾ ᱱᱚᱶᱟ ᱠᱷᱟᱱ ᱜᱮ [[ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱯᱷᱮᱭᱟᱨ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ ᱯᱷᱚᱨ ᱵᱮᱥᱴ ᱟᱠᱴᱨᱮᱥ – ᱛᱟᱢᱤᱞ]] ᱧᱟᱢ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟ ᱾ ᱨᱚᱢᱭᱟ ᱫᱚ ᱒᱐᱑᱙ ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱠᱚᱢᱮᱰᱤ ᱰᱨᱟᱢᱟ ''[[ᱠᱳᱱᱪᱮᱢ ᱤᱥᱛᱚᱢ ᱠᱳᱱᱪᱮᱢ ᱠᱚᱥᱛᱚᱢ]]'' ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱠᱷᱟ.ᱛᱤᱨ [[ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱯᱷᱮᱭᱟᱨ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ ᱯᱷᱚᱨ ᱵᱮᱥᱴ ᱥᱚᱯᱳᱨᱴᱤᱝ ᱟᱠᱴᱨᱮᱥ – ᱛᱮᱞᱩᱜᱩ]] ᱧᱟᱢ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟ ᱾ ᱨᱚᱢᱭᱟ ''[[Baahubali (franchise)|ᱵᱟᱦᱩᱵᱚᱲᱤ ᱥᱤᱨᱤᱡᱽ]]'' (᱒᱐᱑᱕-᱑᱗) ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ [[List of Baahubali characters#Sivagami Devi|ᱥᱤᱵᱚᱜᱟᱢᱤ ᱫᱮᱵᱤ]] ᱠᱮᱨᱮᱠᱴᱚᱨ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟ ᱾ ᱡᱟᱦᱟᱸ ᱨᱮ ''[[ᱵᱟᱦᱩᱵᱚᱲᱤ: ᱯᱩᱭᱞᱩ ᱟᱜ]]'' (᱒᱐᱑᱕) ᱫᱚ ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛᱤᱭᱟ. ᱨᱮ ᱡᱷᱚᱛᱚ ᱠᱷᱚᱱ ᱡᱟ.ᱥᱛᱤ ᱠᱟ.ᱣᱰᱤ ᱠᱚᱢᱟᱣ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱛᱟ.ᱞᱠᱟ. ᱨᱮ ᱛᱩᱨᱩᱭ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ ᱴᱷᱟᱶ ᱮᱥᱮᱫ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟ ᱾ ᱟᱨ ''[[ᱵᱟᱦᱩᱵᱚᱲᱤ ᱒: ᱢᱩᱪᱟ.ᱫ ᱟᱜ]]'' (᱒᱐᱑᱗) ᱫᱚ ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛᱤᱭᱟ. ᱨᱮ ᱡᱷᱚᱛᱚ ᱠᱷᱚᱱ ᱡᱟ.ᱥᱛᱤ ᱠᱟ.ᱣᱰᱤ ᱠᱚᱢᱟᱣ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱛᱟ.ᱞᱠᱟ. ᱨᱮ ᱫᱚᱥᱟᱨ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ ᱴᱷᱟᱶ ᱟᱢᱮᱴ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟ ᱾ ᱒᱐᱑᱖ ᱨᱮ ᱨᱚᱢᱭᱟ [[ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱯᱷᱮᱭᱟᱨ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ ᱥᱟᱣᱩᱛᱷ|ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱯᱷᱮᱭᱟᱨ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ]] ᱠᱷᱚᱱ ''[[ᱵᱟᱦᱩᱵᱚᱲᱤ: ᱯᱩᱭᱞᱩ ᱟᱜ]]'' ᱨᱮ ᱟᱠᱴᱤᱝ ᱠᱷᱟ.ᱛᱤᱨ [[ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱯᱷᱮᱭᱟᱨ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ ᱯᱷᱚᱨ ᱵᱮᱥᱴ ᱥᱚᱯᱳᱨᱴᱤᱝ ᱟᱠᱴᱨᱮᱥ – ᱛᱮᱞᱩᱜᱩ|ᱵᱮᱥᱴ ᱥᱚᱯᱳᱨᱴᱤᱝ ᱟᱠᱴᱨᱮᱥ – ᱛᱮᱞᱩᱜᱩ]] ᱧᱟᱢ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟ ᱾ [[ᱟᱸᱫᱷᱨᱚ ᱯᱨᱚᱫᱮᱥ ᱥᱚᱨᱠᱟᱨ]] ᱯᱟᱦᱴᱟ ᱠᱷᱚᱱ [[ᱱᱚᱱᱫᱤᱱᱤ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ]] ᱦᱚᱛᱮᱛᱮ [[ᱱᱚᱱᱫᱤᱱᱤ ᱟᱣᱟᱨᱰ ᱯᱷᱚᱨ ᱵᱮᱥᱴ ᱥᱚᱯᱳᱨᱴᱤᱝ ᱟᱠᱴᱨᱮᱥ|ᱵᱮᱥᱴ ᱥᱚᱯᱳᱨᱴᱤᱝ ᱟᱠᱴᱨᱮᱥ]] ᱥᱤᱨᱯᱷᱟ.ᱭ ᱧᱟᱢ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟ ᱾

==ᱟᱬᱜᱟᱛ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ==
Ramya was born in [[Madras]] (present-day [[Chennai]]) to Krishnan and Maya.<ref name="bdt"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://celebritykick.com/telugu-actress/ramya-krishnan-family|title=Ramya Krishnan's family|accessdate=16 June 2017|publisher=Celebrity Kick}}</ref> She is the niece of veteran Tamil comedian [[Cho Ramaswamy]]. She received initial training in [[Bharathanatyam]], Western and [[Kuchipudi]] dance forms and has given many stage performances.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/eternal-beauty-nilambari-ramya-krishna-celebrates-her-bday-tamil-news-41545.html |title=Eternal beauty 'Nilambari' Ramya Krishnan celebrates her b'day |last= |website=Indiaglitz |date=15 September 2008 |accessdate=22 July 2015}}</ref>

==ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ‌ᱡᱤᱭᱟᱱ==
===ᱰᱮᱵᱩᱴ ᱟᱨ ᱯᱩᱭᱞᱩ ᱡᱤᱭᱟᱱ ᱮᱴᱠᱮᱴᱚᱬᱮ‌ (᱑᱙᱘᱔–᱑᱙᱘᱙)===
Ramya started her acting career in 1984 at the age of 14 in the [[Tamil Cinema|Tamil]] film ''Vellai Manasu'', opposite [[Y. G. Mahendra]]. In 1986, she made her debut in [[Telugu Cinema|Telugu]] with ''Bhale Mithrulu''. Both the films went unnoticed. Then she went onto play supporting roles in Tamil which includes [[Padikkadavan (1985 film)|Padikkadavan]] starring [[Rajinikanth]] and [[Per Sollum Pillai]] starring [[Kamal Haasan]] in Tamil.

===ᱟᱠᱴᱤᱝ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ ᱟᱨ ᱠᱟ.ᱣᱰᱤ ᱡᱤᱛᱠᱟ.ᱨ ᱫᱟᱲᱮ (᱑᱙᱘᱙–᱑᱙᱙᱘)===
After a series of failures in both Tamil and Telugu, she achieved fame through [[Kasinadhuni Viswanath]]'s ''[[Sutradharulu]]'', released in 1989. The film went onto win [[National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Telugu]]. As her breakthrough came from [[K. Raghavendra Rao]] directorial movies where she emerged as a commercial romantic diva of the season, due to successful movies such as ''[[Alludugaru]]'' (1990), ''[[Allari Mogudu]]'' (1992), ''[[Major Chandrakanth (1993 film)|Major Chandrakanth]]'' (1993) along with [[Mohan Babu]] and ''[[Allari Priyudu]]'' (1993) along with [[Rajasekhar (actor)|Rajasekhar]]. Her performance in [[Allari Priyudu]] received praise from audience. She emerged as a leading actress in the [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] industry alongside [[Soundarya]], [[Meena (actress)|Meena]], [[Roja (actress)|Roja]] and [[Nagma]] in the 1990s. Her films with [[Nagarjuna]] received a widespread praise from audience in the films like [[Hello Brother (1994 film)|Hello Brother]], [[Criminal (1994 film)|Criminal]], [[Gharana Bullodu]], [[Annamayya]] and [[Chandralekha (1998 film)|Chandralekha]]. She played the role of a devoted wife of [[Sri Annamacharya]], which was played by [[Nagarjuna]] in the film ''[[Annamayya]]'' (1997). In 1998, she played a leading role in [[Kante Koothurne Kanu]]. She received a prestigious [[Nandi Award for Best Actress]] from the [[Government of Andhra Pradesh]] for her performance in the film. 

Ramya made her debut in [[Hindi Cinema|Hindi]] in [[Parampara]] under [[Yash Chopra]] direction. Then she acted in few hindi films includes [[Subhash Ghai]]'s [[Khalnayak]], [[Mahesh Bhatt]]'s [[Chaahat (1996 film)|Chaahat]] and [[David Dhawan]]'s [[Banarasi Babu (1997 film)|Banarasi Babu]] and [[Bade Miyan Chote Miyan]]  along with [[Amitabh Bachchan]] and [[Govinda (actor)|Govinda]].

===ᱛᱟᱢᱤᱞᱤ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ ᱛᱮ ᱨᱩᱣᱟ.ᱲ ᱦᱮᱢ===
After four years break from Tamil cinema, In 1999, Ramya played the female antagonistic role in the Tamil film ''[[Padayappa]]'' along with [[Rajinikanth]]. Her performance in the film as "Neelambari" received a much critical acclaim. The critic from [[Rediff]] stated "Ramya does a fantastic job. She is vicious to her dying breath, when she declares she will revenge herself in her next life. She does a fabulous tandav of rage when her father commits suicide" <ref name="nadar">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/1999/apr/28pada.htm |title=Rajni does it again |last=Nadar |first=Ganesh |date=28 April 1999 |publisher=Rediff |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141226055558/http://www.rediff.com/movies/1999/apr/28pada.htm |archive-date=26 December 2014 |access-date=26 December 2014}}</ref>.She went onto receive several awards including [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress - Tamil]] and [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award Special Prize]].  She then starred in commercially successful films like [[Paattali]], [[Budget Padmanabhan]] and [[Panchatanthiram]]. Her performance in [[Panchatanthiram]] as "Maggie" received critical acclaim. The critic from [[Screen (magazine)|Screen]] praised as her "one of the finest performances ever"<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.cscsarchive.org:8081/MediaArchive/art.nsf/(docid)/2EC3A7FCA04F3FB6E5256BFF0033A9F5 | title=Panchathanthiram | publisher=[[Screen (magazine)|Screen]] | date=19 July 2002 | accessdate=4 June 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120322151649/http://www.cscsarchive.org:8081/MediaArchive/art.nsf/(docid)/2EC3A7FCA04F3FB6E5256BFF0033A9F5 | archivedate=22 March 2012}}</ref>.
In her career, Ramya played a Goddess role in many films includes, highly acclaimed [[Ammoru]],[[Rajakali Amman]] and [[Annai Kaligambal]].

===ᱵᱟᱦᱩᱵᱚᱲᱤ ᱟᱨ ᱥᱚᱢᱟᱞᱳᱪᱚᱱᱟ===
In 2015, Ramya acted in an [[S.S. Rajamouli]]'s fantasy multi-starrer [[Baahubali: The Beginning]] and its sequel [[Baahubali: The Conclusion]], where she played Rajamata Sivagami. Her performance met with the critical acclaim and the film becomes the [[List of highest-grossing Indian films|Highest grossing Indian film]] in India. Sangeetha Devi Dundoo praised Ramya's performance and stated "Ramya Krishnan once again aces with her part"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/baahubali-review-a-befitting-conclusion/article18268254.ece|title=Baahubali 2: a befitting conclusion|author=Sangeetha Devi Dundoo|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=28 April 2017|accessdate=4 June 2020}}</ref>.She received [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actress - Telugu]] for both films. After the success of Baahubali, she reunited with [[Mohan Babu]] in [[Mama Manchu Alludu Kanchu]] and [[Nagarjuna]] in [[Soggade Chinni Nayana]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/mohan-babu-act-ramya-meena-allari-nareshs-mama-manchu-alludu-kanchu-639466|title=Mohan Babu is all thrilled to work with Ramya Krishnan and Meena again, 23 years after the release of "Allari Mogudu".|last= |newspaper=ibtimes.co.in |date= |accessdate=16 July 2015}}</ref>. In 2019, she played a porn actress in critically acclaimed [[Super Deluxe (film)|Super Deluxe]] directed by [[Thiagarajan Kumararaja]]. Srivatsan S from [[The Hindu]] stated her role as "boldest role yet"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/super-deluxe-review-believe-the-hype/article26671414.ece|title='Super Deluxe' review: an unusual film with an assortment of quirky characters|first=Srivatsan|last=S|date=29 March 2019|via=www.thehindu.com|newspaper=The Hindu}}</ref>.

She made her debut in digital platform with ''[[Queen (web series)|Queen]]'' in 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/celebrities/story/queen-teaser-out-ramya-krishnan-presents-an-interesting-tale-on-j-jayalalithaa-1625528-2019-12-05|title=Queen teaser out; Ramya Krishnan presents an interesting tale of J Jayalalithaa|last=|first=|date=|website=India Today|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>.The Series received much acclaim for its writing and Ramya's performance. The critic from [[India Today]] stated "Ramya Krishnan as the failing actress and a budding politician(the later part of Shakthi's life) puts in a measured performance and it is what stands out in a series that relies heavily on performances"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/binge-watch/story/queen-review-ramya-krishnan-is-a-majestic-political-leader-in-new-web-series-1628671-2019-12-16|title=Queen Review: Ramya Krishnan is a majestic political leader in new web series|publisher=[[India Today]]|date=18 December 2019|accessdate= 4 June 2020}}</ref>.

===ᱠᱟᱱᱱᱟᱰᱟ ᱟᱨ ᱢᱟᱞᱟᱭᱚᱞᱚᱢ ᱯᱷᱤᱞᱢ===
Ramya had worked in Kannada films such as ''[[Gadibidi Ganda]]'', ''[[Mangalyam Tantunanena]]'', ''Neelambari'', ''[[Raktha Kanneeru]]''. In Malayalam, she debut in [[Neram Pularumbol]] along with [[Mohanlal]] and [[Mammootty]]. Her notable film in Malayalam was [[Ore Kadal]] which received [[National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Malayalam]]. 

===ᱴᱮᱞᱤᱵᱷᱤᱡᱚᱱ===
She was a judge in a dancing show on [[STAR Vijay]]: ''[[Jodi Number One]]'', season 1, followed by season 5. She hosted a popular show "Thanga Vettai" on [[Sun TV (India)|Sun TV]] and starred in tele-series like [[Kalasam (TV series)|Kalasam]], [[Thangam (TV series)|Thangam]] and [[Vamsam (TV series)|Vamsam]].

